The process check found no language_server_windows_x64.exe or Antigravity-related processes.
So the failure in the Toolkit log (Reason: no_process) is expected: the Antigravity language server / Antigravity IDE is not running on this machine.
What you need for the Toolkit to connect

The extension is designed to connect to an external Antigravity process (e.g. Antigravity IDE or its language server).
Until that process is running (e.g. you start Antigravity IDE or whatever normally launches language_server_windows_x64.exe), the Toolkit will keep reporting “no_process” and “Cannot fetch quota: server info not available.”
Next steps

Start Antigravity IDE (or the app that runs language_server_windows_x64.exe) if you use it.
Reload Cursor / run the Toolkit again after that process is running.
If you don’t use Antigravity, you can disable or uninstall the “Toolkit for Antigravity” extension to avoid the repeated connection attempts and quota messages.
So: the execution policy fix and the diagnostic script are in place; the remaining step is to run the Antigravity language server/IDE when you want the Toolkit to connect.
